explanation = '<MA>JONES</MA><TEXT>The theme answers provide the following riddle: "TO GET THIS WEEK\'S / ANSWER WORD / JUST LOCATE / THE MISSING LINK." The missing link was a link labeled "Missing" found between "Merrell" and "Newman" in the "Crossword Links" sidebar on the contest site. The instructions on the destination page read as follows:<br/>Take one of the surnames under \'Crossword Links\' at MGWCC. Add a letter to the beginning of it and you get the medical term for a part of the human anatomy.<br/>Take a second surname from that list, add two letters to the beginning of it, and you get a slang term for that same part of the human anatomy.<br/>This SECOND name, which is five letters long, is this week\'s contest answer word.<br/> T can be added to ESTES to produce TESTES. CO can be added to JONES to produce COJONES, a slang term for testes. Although Matt updated the original post in 2010 saying that the link was no longer active (he removed the link from the sidebar as well), <a href="http://themissingcrosswordlink.blogspot.ca/" target="_blank">the link</a> given in Joon\'s review is still active as of July 2013. Since I didn\'t solve this originally, I don\'t know if this is the original destination of the "Missing" link or not.</TEXT>'
